The paper discusses the generation of random bits, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of biased coin flips and dice rolls, which are related to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes a procedure for entropy-preserving binarization, which could be relevant to coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI).
